TY  - CASE
TI  - Brown v. Board of Education
PB  - United States Supreme Court
VL  - 347
SP  - 483
PY  - 1954
AB  - Landmark Supreme Court decision that declared racial segregation in public schools unconstitutional. The Court held that "separate but equal" educational facilities are inherently unequal, thereby overturning Plessy v. Ferguson (1896). Chief Justice Earl Warren delivered the unanimous opinion.
