AU  - Holmes, Oliver Wendell
JO  - Harvard Law Review
VL  - 10
IS  - 8
SP  - 457
EP  - 478
PY  - 1897
SN  - 0017-811X
AB  - In this seminal essay, Justice Oliver Wendell Holmes Jr. articulates his legal realist philosophy, arguing that law should be studied as a predictive science rather than as a system of moral principles. Holmes famously defines law as predictions of what courts will do in fact.
